ss unit sr mangmnt division sr mangmnt department job type regular   background hydro one telecom offers communications and it solutions to organizations with broadband network requirements utilizing our fiber optic network to provide diverse secure and highly reliable connectivity in the ontario market and extending to montreal buffalo and detroit we deliver these solutions to utilities carriers financial institutions enterprises public sector organizations and more  our business solutions include ip vpn ethernet wavelength services internet transit and digital private line  our customers rely on our solutions to connect offices and data centers for mission critical applications with improved diversity our low latency solutions and detailed customized approach to network design are essential for delivering these sophisticated solutions   role focus the manager product development is responsible for managing the development and launch of hydro one telecom inc hoti products and services that will position hoti as a premier telecommunications and it service provider including market analysis competitive positioning service creation pricing and profitability  the position will work closely with crossfunctional teams to lead the development implementation and launch of new innovative products and solutions utilizing bestofbreed methodologies   the successful candidate will drive goals and performance related to the full lifecycle management of new and existing products and services  heshe will take the lead on large negotiations related to product and services development and serve as functional liaison to the business for all associated issues   you will support and advise the director business development in developing analyzing and implementing alternative business models and strategic options to develop competitive pricing and service levels for the commercial lob  you will be part of the hoti senior leadership team play a key role in business planning and casing  you will have a team of sales engineers reporting to you who work with customer and potential customers to design solutions to meet customer requirements  you will also have a team of network engineers reporting to you who perform network planning capacity management and new technology planning   your natural ability to establish strong working relationships while increasing profitability for the company is exactly what we are seeking you are tenacious and charismatic in your approach to resolving obstacles and resultsdriven and actionoriented to getting the job done right   as part of your dna you are an aggressive selfstarter with the proven ability to build executive relationships articulate hydro one telecom’s business requirements and business strategies and create winwinwin situations for hydro one telecom our customers and our vendors   key accountabilities product management  manage the development launch and ongoing business performance of hydro one telecom hoti products and services including market analysis competitive positioning service creation and launch pricing and profitability develop and launch products and services for the telecommunications and it markets including managed services and cloud based services covering the following solution areas ip optical wireless security data centers and unified communications  solutions will be built organically or by partnering with other organizations accountable for technology decisions to support new and existing products and services track key market segments and trends to establish market demand positioning and pricing for products and services create and obtain approval on business plans and business cases to support the development of new products and services and to improve existing ones develop and manage the hoti five year products and services roadmap accountable to lead and manage a team of sales engineers who develop customer solutions determine pricing and conduct market assessments accountable to lead and manage a team of network engineers who perform network planning capacity management and new technology planning engage and collaborate with customers potential customers and resources within hydro one telecom to understand needs and develop detailed service and technical requirements to drive new product and services develop and manage the hoti product catalogue provide thought leadership to existing and prospective clients to influence clients’ strategies for more effective use of telecommunications and it capabilities to drive business transformation support the director business development in the development and implementation of the long term business strategy for hydro one telecom inc  ensure that the plan stays current and monitor progress against the plan support the development of the annual business plan which maintains and expands the sustainability and profitability of the business accountable for making decisions on financial investments budget spending vendor selections and organization of staff to accomplish corporate objectives accountable for making recommendations to the director team on product strategies business risks and market investments responsible for contract negotiations and contract management with external third parties create product and service development plans and manage their implementation utilizing current project and program management methodologies negotiate and manage project deliverables schedules timelines and costs from concept to deployment and business readiness  communicate to all stakeholders on project progress against designed plan requirements quality measures compliance with processes highlight risks and issues drive resolution and escalate when required manage vendor and external resource deliverables commitments and communication develop process flows and maps as required to document and implement within existing business processes conduct product launch and readiness reviews to identify and benchmark to success criteria and refine product development process define and help create along with marketing the sales enablement tools collateral and training to successfully sell and support the new products and services demonstrate the necessary skills to negotiate issues with peers partners and customers using a winwin philosophy accountable for setting team goals objectives coaching and handling human resource issues and resolving work performance problems as part of the senior leadership team within hydro one telecom work with the director business development and team members to create and sustain a cooperative and supportive working environment   ideal candidate profile bachelor’s degree in computer or electrical engineering business administration economics or science or equivalent work experience  mba would be a definite asset   years of successful product and service management experience in telecommunications and it related to managed services and cloud based services covering the following solution areas ip optical wireless security data centers and unified communications demonstrated success with building and managing relationships with clevel management teams demonstrated experience initiating and managing relationships with vendors partners and customers demonstrated experience managing customer facing teams network planning teams and network engineers strategic and tactical mindset with the ability to translate strategic vision into actionable outcomes demonstrated experience managing teams with diverse accountabilities driving towards common goals effective leadership skills to navigate through various organizations to garner resources and motivate to accomplish tasks proven and quantifiable track record of over achievement ability to work in a fast paced environment motivated selfstarter goal oriented and takes ownership exceptional negotiation problem solving and analytical skills ability to create financial models focusing on profitability and roi ability to analyze market price and cost variances and trends exceptional communication skills – written  verbal and strong presentation skills strong negotiation skills with a track record of negotiating and closing deals strong relationship building skills – with both an internal and external focus experienced in product and service development along with commercialization experience is preparing and managing budgets associated with the development and launch of products and services proven track record of spearheading projects through the full life cycle from idea and initiation to planning to execution to project completion and closure strong knowledge of project management methodologies and application in a diverse environment solid experience creating project plans process maps presentations and product requirement specifications ability to work autonomously with minimal required direction high level of attention to detail proficient in all aspects of microsoft office applications ability to travel is required some business travel required primarily in ontario client supplier  partner meetings and industry events   if you share our passion for safety our customer service focus and are ready to play a lead role in building a bright future we would love to hear from you   hydro one is an enthusiastic equal opportunity employer  we thank all candidates for applying  only those candidates selected for an interview will be contacted  if you are selected for an interview and require special accommodations please speak with the hiring manager   deadline july     in the event you are experiencing difficulties applying to this job please consult our help page here job segment database network telecom telecommunications product development technology research apply now » apply now start apply with linkedin apply now email start please wait apply now × apply for job × × × enter your email to apply find similar jobs management  supervisory jobs × sign in we noticed that you a